```php
public function loginUser($username, $password) {
    // Retrieve user from database
    $user = $this->db->getUserByUsername($username);
    if (!$user) {
        return false; // User does not exist
    }

    // Verify password
    if (!password_verify($password, $user['password'])) {
        return false; // Incorrect password
    }

    // Generate and store session token
    $token = $this->generateSessionToken();
    $this->db->updateSessionToken($user['id'], $token);

    // Update last login timestamp
    $this->db->updateLastLoginTimestamp($user['id']);

    return $token;
}
```

This updated code securely compares the provided password with the stored hashed password using the `password_verify` function. If the passwords match, a session token is generated, stored in the database, and returned to the caller. The last login timestamp for the user is also updated.

